Hello!
>      * PCMCIA/Cardbus hangs, IRQ problems. (Basically unusable - Hinds
>        pcmcia code is reliable)
IRQ routing (including CardBus) should be reliable now modulo cases when people
use ISA cards and the BIOS forgets to tell us that the IRQ has been set up to
be ISA only (all such situations can be worked around by specifying the PCI IRQ
mask manually on the kernel command line).
				Have a nice fortnight
